description: From Latin circumvallare, from circum- + vallum (“rampart”).

entries.meaning: Surrounded with a wall; enclosed with a rampart.
(anatomy) Surrounded by a ridge or elevation.
examples: circumvallate papillae, near the base of the tongue

verbs.description: circumvallate (third-person singular simple present circumvallates, present participle circumvallating, simple past and past participle circumvallated)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To surround with, or as if with, a rampart.
